276
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:27,360
from science uses them in a kind of poaching way.

277
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:30,040
You sort of go into somebody else's territory,

278
00:15:30,040 --> 00:15:33,280
take what you need, you're not explaining it.

279
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:36,600
You're communicating something entirely else that

280
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:37,800
can't be reduced to words.

281
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:40,200
So I'll stop there.

282
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:43,760
In the spirit of contradiction, I would say that one thing

283
00:15:43,760 --> 00:15:45,160
I've picked up from this conference

284
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:48,160
is the similarities between art and science,

285
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:51,840
that if they're both sort of an investigation of the world

286
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:56,440
as we know it, and so little of what we do in school

287
00:15:56,440 --> 00:16:00,680
and in society is really talk about the real world,

288
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:04,280
the physical world we live in.

289
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:07,320
And so both art and science are largely

