00:23:30,880 --> 00:23:32,920
Can we change the world?

400
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:38,880
At the same time, points to something that I think is more prevalent now

401
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:45,280
than perhaps once was, which is all of these things have ethical dimensions.

402
00:23:45,280 --> 00:23:50,440
So it's something that I think scientists are thinking more about.

403
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:56,960
I think artists are just assuming as part of the project in a way

404
00:23:56,960 --> 00:24:01,720
that maybe wasn't true 40 years ago or 50 years ago.

405
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:05,200
Yeah, especially when you consider we're experiencing exponential growth

406
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:10,040
and technology, whether or not we're going to have artificial intelligence

407
00:24:10,040 --> 00:24:13,680
in 50 or 100 years is relevant.

408
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:21,480
It's coming, and the moral and ethical implications for that are ambiguous.

409
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:27,480
And because of this advances in technology, it's also we live in an age

410
00:24:27,480 --> 00:24:31,280
where I think religion is losing its relevance.

411
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:39,800
And I think that the arts can step up and be the moral conscience of our species.

412
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:42,520
I think it's a duty, in fact.

